@node introduction "x-files - introduction"

                              introduction

the fourth issue is here and this time hopefully without an error. in the last
issue there where an error with the showing of the title-picture.
this time i hope that there will be no errors...

i am searching for an iff-converter, which is able to convert aga-pics into
executable files. the executable file should not need any external files
(like libraries, ...) if it is executed. till now the search for a program
was not successfull, so i use in this issue the old display-tool from the
workbench disk.
if you have a tool which is able to do the things mentioned above, please
send it to me... :-)

i want to thank all the people, who sent me news and other stuff.
this time the support was really great, as you can see (number of groups in
this issue is above 50).
but don't think that i don't need more support... i caaaaaaaaaaaan't get
enough.... :-)
so keep on sending me every news or information you have... thanx !!!


ok, thanx for now and see ya soon...


                                big-rat

@endnode

